## Verification Protocol

Every technical value must be 2-layer verified before writing code:
1. Check reference files in `.cursor/references/`
2. Verify against actual source code (npm types, function signatures)

If they conflict -> source code wins. Do not assume function names from memory - grep first.

## Input Handling

User-submitted encrypted values arrive as `externalEuintXX` + `bytes calldata inputProof`.
Convert with `FHE.fromExternal(encAmount, inputProof)` - this verifies the ZK proof.
`FHE.asEuint64(42)` converts a Solidity literal, NOT user-submitted inputs.

## ACL - Required After Every Stored Computation

- `FHE.allowThis(result)` - contract keeps access in future transactions
- `FHE.allow(result, user)` - user can decrypt their own data
- `FHE.allowTransient(result, target)` - cross-contract access within same tx

Without `allowThis`, the contract reverts with `SenderNotAllowed(address)` (custom error from `@fhevm/host-contracts/contracts/ACL.sol:106`) on the next transaction.

## Encrypted Conditionals

```solidity
/* WRONG - Solidity compile error: ebool is bytes32 UDVT, no implicit bool conversion */
require(FHE.le(amount, balance));

/* CORRECT */
ebool hasEnough = FHE.le(amount, balance);
euint64 newBal = FHE.select(hasEnough, FHE.sub(balance, amount), balance);
```

## Comparison Names (exact - alternatives do not compile)

`FHE.ne()` not `neq()` | `FHE.le()` not `lte()` | `FHE.ge()` not `gte()`

## Public Decryption (3-step, dApp-driven)

1. `FHE.makePubliclyDecryptable(handle)` - permanent, irreversible
2. Off-chain: relayer SDK `publicDecrypt([handle])` -> `results.clearValues[handle]`
3. `FHE.checkSignatures(bytes32[] cts, bytes cleartexts, bytes proof)` - handle order must match step 2

## Types

| Type | Arithmetic | Comparison | Notes |
|------|-----------|------------|-------|
| ebool | - | eq, ne | and/or/xor/not, select, rand |
| euint8-128 | full (div/rem plaintext-only) | full | select, rand, neg, not, bitwise, shift/rotate |
| eaddress | - | eq, ne | select only (no arithmetic, no ordering) |
| euint160 | - | - | declared in `encrypted-types/EncryptedTypes.sol` but `@fhevm/solidity@0.11.1` exposes ZERO `FHE.*` overloads; any operation fails with `Member "<op>" not found ... after argument-dependent lookup`. Use `eaddress` for 160-bit values. |
| euint256 | - | eq, ne | bitwise, shift/rotate, select, neg, not, rand |
| eint8-eint256 | declared, no ops | declared, no ops | declared as `bytes32` types in `encrypted-types/EncryptedTypes.sol` so a bare `eint64 x;` compiles; `@fhevm/solidity@0.11.1` ships zero `FHE.*` overloads, so the first call fails with `Member "<op>" not found ... after argument-dependent lookup` |

## Quick Reference: Encrypted Operations

| Operation | Function | Types | Notes |
|-----------|----------|-------|-------|
| Add | `FHE.add(a, b)` | euint8-128 | Wraps on overflow |
| Subtract | `FHE.sub(a, b)` | euint8-128 | Wraps on underflow |
| Multiply | `FHE.mul(a, b)` | euint8-128 | Expensive HCU |
| Divide | `FHE.div(a, plaintext)` | euint8-128 | Plaintext RHS ONLY |
| Compare eq | `FHE.eq(a, b)` | all | Returns ebool |
| Compare ne | `FHE.ne(a, b)` | all | NOT neq |
| Compare le | `FHE.le(a, b)` | euint8-128 | NOT lte |
| Compare lt | `FHE.lt(a, b)` | euint8-128 | |
| Compare ge | `FHE.ge(a, b)` | euint8-128 | NOT gte |
| Compare gt | `FHE.gt(a, b)` | euint8-128 | |
| Conditional | `FHE.select(cond, a, b)` | all | Encrypted ternary |
| Random | `FHE.randEuintX()` | all euint | On-chain RNG |
| Min/Max | `FHE.min/max(a, b)` | euint8-128 | |
| Bitwise | `FHE.and/or/xor/not` | all except eaddress | |
| Shift | `FHE.shl/shr/rotl/rotr` | euint8-256 | Modulo bit width |

