## Workflow: Generate Contract

When the user asks to create a new FHEVM contract:

1. **Tier 1 preload** -> `.cursor/references/anti-patterns.md` (always) + `.cursor/references/code-style.md`.
2. **Determine use case** (token, voting, auction, access control, custom). Pick the matching template from `.cursor/templates/` (`ConfidentialERC20.sol`, `PrivateVoting.sol`, `SealedAuction.sol`) when available.
3. **Tier 2 preload on demand** -> `types-operations.md`, `acl.md`, `inputs-decryption.md`, `erc7984.md` as the feature requires.
4. **Write the contract**, enforcing the ALWAYS / NEVER rules above on every line; cite the rule number when making non-obvious choices.
5. **Deliver only after** the Self-Review Checklist and Post-Delivery Grep below both return zero failures.

## Workflow: Review Contract

When the user asks to review existing FHEVM code:

1. **Tier 1 preload** -> Read `.cursor/references/anti-patterns.md` (all verified mistakes, auto-loads on every review)
2. **Phase 1 - Static Scan** (for each function):
   - Trace all encrypted value flows (creation -> operation -> storage)
   - Verify ACL: every stored value has `allowThis()`, every user value has `allow()`
   - Check: no branching on encrypted values (`require`/`if`/`assert`)
   - Check: all external inputs use `fromExternal()`, not `asEuintXX()`
   - Check: comparison functions use correct names (`ne` not `neq`, `le` not `lte`)
   - Scan for all documented anti-patterns
3. **Phase 2 - Logic Analysis**:
   - Can any operation overflow? Is it guarded with `FHE.select`?
   - Can any division have an encrypted divisor?
   - Are `checkSignatures` handle orders consistent with `publicDecrypt` order?
   - Are there uninitialized handles being used in operations?
4. **Phase 3 - 2-Layer Verify** every candidate finding against installed source (`node_modules/@fhevm/solidity/lib/FHE.sol`). Reject findings that Layer 2 disproves.
5. **Phase 4 - Classify with three tags**. Every finding carries:
   - **Confidence** (0-100): `DEFINITE BUG` (>=95), `LIKELY ISSUE` (80-94), `PROBABLE ISSUE` (70-79), `SUGGESTION` (40-69), `NOTE` (<40)
   - **Severity** (impact-based): `Critical` (funds/lockup/confidentiality breach), `High`, `Medium`, `Low`, `Info`
   - **Remark** (reviewer judgement): `Exploitable`, `Needs Review`, `Design Choice`, `False Positive`, `Hardening`
6. **Phase 5 - Output** as a Findings Summary table with columns: `# | Severity | Confidence | Category | Location | Remark | Title` - sort by Severity (Critical -> Info) then Confidence desc. Each finding detail carries a header line `Severity - Confidence N - Remark`. Include fix diff when Confidence >= 80; otherwise a one-line Suggested Mitigation.

## Workflow: Deploy Contract

When the user asks to deploy, set up a project, or configure deployment:

1. **Tier 1 preload** -> `.cursor/references/anti-patterns.md` (config mistakes #22a and #23-#25).
2. **Tier 2 preload** -> `.cursor/references/environment.md` and `.cursor/references/deployment.md`.
3. Framework is Hardhat. Two deploy patterns:
   - Path A (default): `npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.ts --network <net>`. Template https://github.com/zunmax/fhevm-template.
   - Path B: `hardhat-deploy@^0.11.45` plugin. Same template (https://github.com/zunmax/fhevm-template) ships `contracts/deploy/deploy.ts`; run with `npx hardhat deploy --network <net>`.
4. Required pins: `hardhat@^2.28.6` (pin v2 explicitly - bare `npm install hardhat` resolves v3 and breaks; the plugin itself only peers `hardhat ^2.0.0`), `@fhevm/hardhat-plugin@^0.4.2`, `@fhevm/mock-utils@^0.4.2`, `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk@0.4.1` (EXACT, no caret - mock-utils peers it that way and the plugin runtime-aborts on drift), `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-ethers@^3.1.3`, `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-chai-matchers@^2.1.2`, `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-network-helpers@^1.1.2` (opt-in), `hardhat-deploy@^0.11.45` (Path B). Do NOT install `hardhat-deploy@^0.12`, `hardhat-deploy@^2.0`, `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-ethers@^4.x`, or `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-network-helpers@^3.x`: all require Hardhat 3.
5. Compiler: Solidity `0.8.28`, `evmVersion: "cancun"`, optimizer `runs: 800`. Bump pragma to `^0.8.27`+ if importing `@openzeppelin/confidential-contracts`.
6. Config: `.env` via `dotenv` (`PRIVATE_KEY`, `RPC_URL`, `ETHERSCAN_API_KEY`). Etherscan v2 uses a single `apiKey` string.
7. Write deploy script matching the chosen path. Persist address + ABI to `deployments/<network>/<Contract>.json`.
8. Grep output for anti-patterns #22a (missing version pin) and #23-#25 (wrong relayer URL, v0.8 addresses, hardcoded config).
9. Run the deployment checklist from `deployment.md` before delivering.

## Workflow: Security Audit

When the user says "audit", "security review", "deep review", or "full review":

**Orchestrated mode (preferred, when the harness supports parallel sub-agents):** spawn 7 specialized hacking modules in parallel, each reading its bundle of source + module-specific instructions. The 7 bundles live under `.cursor/review-modules/` paired with `.cursor/references/`:

| Bundle | Files (appended in order) |
|--------|---------------------------|
| `module-1-bundle.md` | `references/fhe-vulnerabilities.md` + `review-modules/encrypted-state-flow.md` + `review-modules/audit-protocol.md` |
| `module-2-bundle.md` | `review-modules/acl-completeness.md` + `review-modules/audit-protocol.md` |
| `module-3-bundle.md` | `review-modules/decryption-integrity.md` + `review-modules/audit-protocol.md` |
| `module-4-bundle.md` | `review-modules/type-operation-safety.md` + `review-modules/audit-protocol.md` |
| `module-5-bundle.md` | `review-modules/confidentiality-boundary.md` + `review-modules/audit-protocol.md` |
| `module-6-bundle.md` | `review-modules/fhe-logic-invariant.md` + `review-modules/audit-protocol.md` |
| `module-7-bundle.md` | `references/solidity-vulnerabilities.md` + `review-modules/solidity-security.md` + `review-modules/audit-protocol.md` |

After all modules report, deduplicate by `group_key = Contract | function | vulnerability-class`, gate-evaluate per `finding-validation.md`, and emit one report per `report-format.md` with the ACL Coverage Matrix.

**Single-agent mode (when parallel spawning is unavailable):**

1. **Tier 1 preload** -> `.cursor/references/fhe-vulnerabilities.md` (32 FHE patterns P1-P32) + `.cursor/references/solidity-vulnerabilities.md` (29 Solidity patterns G1-G29)
2. **Tier 2 preload** -> `.cursor/references/finding-validation.md` (4-gate scoring) + `.cursor/references/report-format.md` (output template)
3. **Scan each in-scope `.sol` file** against all 61 patterns. Category map:
   - FHE-specific (P1-P32): Encrypted State Corruption (P1-P5), ACL Permission Gaps (P6-P10), Decryption Flow (P11-P14), Type System Violations (P15-P19), Confidentiality Boundary (P20-P23), Cross-Contract Risks (P24-P27), Logic Errors (P28-P32). Full descriptions in `fhe-vulnerabilities.md`.
   - General Solidity (G1-G29): Reentrancy (G1-G3), Access Control (G4-G7), Token Integration (G8-G12), Math / Precision (G13-G18), Execution Flow (G19-G22), Proxy / Upgrade (G23-G25), Economic / Oracle (G26-G29). Full descriptions in `solidity-vulnerabilities.md`.
4. **Validate every candidate finding** through the 4 gates in `finding-validation.md`: Refutation, Reachability, Trigger, Impact.
5. **Tag each finding** with Confidence (0-100), Severity, Remark as defined above. Confidence >= 80 gets description + fix diff; below 80 gets description only.
6. **Emit report** per `report-format.md`, including the ACL Coverage Matrix.

